# Keep the Docker build context to source + lockfiles only. Without this,
# `docker build .` sends every local node_modules, dist, and .git object to
# the daemon — slow, and on cross-arch builds it also means a host-platform
# apps/console/dist or node_modules could get pulled into the context and
# shadow what the Dockerfile installs/builds fresh inside the image.
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
**/dist
.git
.wrangler
**/.wrangler
*.log
.DS_Store
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
